{{Nihongo|'''''Tengai Makyou: Ziria'''''|天外魔境 ZIRIA|Tengai Makyō Jiraia}}, also known as '''''Far East of Eden: Ziria''''', is a 1989 [[role-playing video game]], which published by [[Hudson Soft]] on [[PC Engine]] [[CD-ROM²]]. It is the first game in the ''[[Tengai Makyo]]'' (''Far East of Eden'') series, and follows a plot based on the legend of [[Jiraiya]]. The game was popular in Japan because its release on the [[CD-ROM]] format, which made it a large game for its time filled with voiced [[cutscenes]] and [[CD audio]] music.

