== Release ==
{{Expand section|date=December 2023}}
The game was re-released for Japanese cellphones in the 2000s.<ref>{{Cite web |title=ハドソン、FOMAのPCエンジンコーナーに「天外魔境ZIRIA」 |url=https://k-tai.watch.impress.co.jp/cda/article/news_toppage/21814.html |access-date=2023-12-25 |website=k-tai.watch.impress.co.jp}}</ref>

An [[Xbox 360]] remake {{nihongo|'''''Tengai Makyou: Ziria &ndash; Haruka naru Jipang'''''|天外魔境 ZIRIA～遥かなるジパング～ || lit. "Far East of Eden Ziria: Tales from Distant Jipang"{{citation needed|date=March 2015}} }} was released in 2006. [[Gaijinworks]] was working on an English localization of the remake at some point, but had to cancel the project due to being unable to get past [[Microsoft]]'s publishing minimums.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://gematsu.com/2015/05/screenshots-gaijinworks-cancelled-far-east-eden-ziria-localization | title=Screenshots of Gaijinworks' cancelled Far East of Eden: Ziria localization| date=2015-05-25}}</ref>

In 2023, an English-language [[Fan translation of video games|fan translation]] of the game was released.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Handley |first1=Zoey |title=PC-Engine CD RPG Tengai Makyou: Ziria get fan translated |url=https://www.destructoid.com/pc-engine-cd-rpg-tengai-makyou-ziria-get-fan-translated/ |website=[[Destructoid]] |access-date=11 December 2023}}</ref>

== Reception ==
The game received a positive review from ''[[PC Engine Fan]]'' magazine, which rated it 25.67 out of 30.<ref name="PCEF">{{cite journal |title=ROLEPLAYING GAME |journal=[[PC Engine Fan]] |issue=PC Engine All Catalog '92: PC Engine Fan Appendix |date=August 1992 |lang=ja |pages=33-48 (40-1) |url=https://archive.org/details/pc-engine-all-catalog-92-pc-engine-fan-appendix-august-1992/PC%20Engine%20All%20Catalog%20%2792%20-%20PC%20Engine%20Fan%20Appendix%20%28August%201992%29/page/40/mode/2up}}</ref>

